msgctxt "mn73:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 73 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 73 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn73:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvacchasutta "
msgstr "The Longer Discourse With Vacchagotta "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn73:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn73:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn73:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho vacchagotto paribbājako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then the wanderer Vacchagotta went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn73:2.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha, "

#. REF: nya3
msgctxt "mn73:3.1"
msgid "“dīgharattāhaṃ bhotā gotamena sahakathī. "
msgstr "“For a long time I have had discussions with Master Gotama. "

msgctxt "mn73:3.2"
msgid "Sādhu me bhavaṃ gotamo saṃkhittena kusalākusalaṃ desetū”ti. "
msgstr "Please teach me in brief what is skillful and what is unskillful.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:3.3"
msgid "“Saṃkhittenapi kho te ahaṃ, vaccha, kusalākusalaṃ deseyyaṃ, vitthārenapi kho te ahaṃ, vaccha, kusalākusalaṃ deseyyaṃ; "
msgstr "“Vaccha, I can teach you what is skillful and what is unskillful in brief or in detail. "

msgctxt "mn73:3.4"
msgid "api ca te ahaṃ, vaccha, saṃkhittena kusalākusalaṃ desessāmi. "
msgstr "Still, let me do so in brief. "

msgctxt "mn73:3.5"
msgid "Taṃ suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi, bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:3.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Vaccha replied. "

msgctxt "mn73:3.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, sc2
msgctxt "mn73:4.1"
msgid "“Lobho kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, alobho kusalaṃ; "
msgstr "“Greed is unskillful, contentment is skillful. "

msgctxt "mn73:4.2"
msgid "doso kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, adoso kusalaṃ; "
msgstr "Hate is unskillful, love is skillful. "

msgctxt "mn73:4.3"
msgid "moho kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, amoho kusalaṃ. "
msgstr "Delusion is unskillful, understanding is skillful. "

msgctxt "mn73:4.4"
msgid "Iti kho, vaccha, ime tayo dhammā akusalā, tayo dhammā kusalā. "
msgstr "So there are these three unskillful things and three that are skillful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, pts-vp-pli1.490, sc3
msgctxt "mn73:5.1"
msgid "Pāṇātipāto kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, pāṇātipātā veramaṇī kusalaṃ; "
msgstr "Killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; covetousness, ill will, and wrong view: these things are unskillful. "

msgctxt "mn73:5.2"
msgid "adinnādānaṃ kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, adinnādānā veramaṇī kusalaṃ; "
msgstr "Refraining from killing living creatures, stealing, and sexual misconduct; refraining from speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; contentment, kind-heartedness, and right view: these things are skillful. "

msgctxt "mn73:5.3"
msgid "kāmesumicchācāro kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, kāmesumicchācārā veramaṇī kusalaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:5.4"
msgid "musāvādo kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, musāvādā veramaṇī kusalaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:5.5"
msgid "pisuṇā vācā kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, pisuṇāya vācāya veramaṇī kusalaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:5.6"
msgid "pharusā vācā kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, pharusāya vācāya veramaṇī kusalaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:5.7"
msgid "samphappalāpo kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, samphappalāpā veramaṇī kusalaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:5.8"
msgid "abhijjhā kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, anabhijjhā kusalaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:5.9"
msgid "byāpādo kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ, abyāpādo kusalaṃ; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:5.10"
msgid "micchādiṭṭhi kho, vaccha, akusalaṃ sammādiṭṭhi kusalaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:5.11"
msgid "Iti kho, vaccha, ime dasa dhammā akusalā, dasa dhammā kusalā. "
msgstr "So there are these ten unskillful things and ten that are skillful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc4
msgctxt "mn73:6.1"
msgid "Yato kho, vaccha, bhikkhuno taṇhā pahīnā hoti ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā, so hoti bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto”ti. "
msgstr "When a mendicant has given up craving so it is cut off at the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the future, that mendicant is perfected. They’ve ended the defilements, completed the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and are rightly freed through enlightenment.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7, sc5
msgctxt "mn73:7.1"
msgid "“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo. "
msgstr "“Leaving aside Master Gotama, "

#. VAR: sāvako yo āsavānaṃ khayā → sāvako āsavānaṃ khayā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn73:7.2"
msgid "Atthi pana te bhoto gotamassa ekabhikkhupi sāvako yo āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti? "
msgstr "is there even a single monk disciple of Master Gotama who has realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:7.3"
msgid "“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye bhikkhū mama sāvakā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti. "
msgstr "“There are not just one hundred such monks who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8, sc6
msgctxt "mn73:8.1"
msgid "“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū. "
msgstr "“Leaving aside Master Gotama and the monks, "

msgctxt "mn73:8.2"
msgid "Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekā bhikkhunīpi sāvikā yā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharatī”ti? "
msgstr "is there even a single nun disciple of Master Gotama who has realized the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and lives having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:8.3"
msgid "“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova yā bhikkhuniyo mama sāvikā āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharantī”ti. "
msgstr "“There are not just one hundred such nuns who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9, pts-vp-pli1.491, sc7
msgctxt "mn73:9.1"
msgid "“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo. "
msgstr "“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, and the nuns, "

msgctxt "mn73:9.2"
msgid "Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsakopi sāvako gihī odātavasano brahmacārī yo pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko tattha parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā”ti? "
msgstr "is there even a single layman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed and celibate—who, with the ending of the five lower fetters, is reborn spontaneously, to be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:9.3"
msgid "“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye upāsakā mama sāvakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyino anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā”ti. "
msgstr "“There are not just one hundred such celibate laymen who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, sc8
msgctxt "mn73:10.1"
msgid "“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino. "
msgstr "“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, the nuns, and the celibate laymen, "

msgctxt "mn73:10.2"
msgid "Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsakopi sāvako gihī odātavasano kāmabhogī sāsanakaro ovādappaṭikaro yo tiṇṇavicikiccho vigatakathaṅkatho vesārajjappatto aparappaccayo satthusāsane viharatī”ti? "
msgstr "is there even a single layman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed, enjoying sensual pleasures, following instructions, and responding to advice—who has gone beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and lives self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instruction?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:10.3"
msgid "“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova ye upāsakā mama sāvakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino sāsanakarā ovādappaṭikarā tiṇṇavicikicchā vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane viharantī”ti. "
msgstr "“There are not just one hundred such laymen enjoying sensual pleasures who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11, sc9
msgctxt "mn73:11.1"
msgid "“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino. "
msgstr "“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, the nuns, the celibate laymen, and the laymen enjoying sensual pleasures, "

msgctxt "mn73:11.2"
msgid "Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsikāpi sāvikā gihinī odātavasanā brahmacārinī yā pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyinī anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā”ti? "
msgstr "is there even a single laywoman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed and celibate—who, with the ending of the five lower fetters, is reborn spontaneously, to be extinguished there, not liable to return from that world?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:11.3"
msgid "“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova yā upāsikā mama sāvikā gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātikā tattha parinibbāyiniyo anāvattidhammā tasmā lokā”ti. "
msgstr "“There are not just one hundred such celibate laywomen who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc10
msgctxt "mn73:12.1"
msgid "“Tiṭṭhatu bhavaṃ gotamo, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhū, tiṭṭhantu bhikkhuniyo, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino, tiṭṭhantu upāsakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino, tiṭṭhantu upāsikā gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo. "
msgstr "“Leaving aside Master Gotama, the monks, the nuns, the celibate laymen, the laymen enjoying sensual pleasures, and the celibate laywomen, "

msgctxt "mn73:12.2"
msgid "Atthi pana bhoto gotamassa ekupāsikāpi sāvikā gihinī odātavasanā kāmabhoginī sāsanakarā ovādappaṭikarā yā tiṇṇavicikicchā vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane viharatī”ti? "
msgstr "is there even a single laywoman disciple of Master Gotama—white-clothed, enjoying sensual pleasures, following instructions, and responding to advice—who has gone beyond doubt, got rid of indecision, and lives self-assured and independent of others regarding the Teacher’s instruction?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:12.3"
msgid "“Na kho, vaccha, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova yā upāsikā mama sāvikā gihiniyo odātavasanā kāmabhoginiyo sāsanakarā ovādappaṭikarā tiṇṇavicikicchā vigatakathaṅkathā vesārajjappattā aparappaccayā satthusāsane viharantī”ti. "
msgstr "“There are not just one hundred such laywomen enjoying sensual pleasures who are my disciples, Vaccha, or two or three or four or five hundred, but many more than that.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, pts-vp-pli1.492, sc11
msgctxt "mn73:13.1"
msgid "“Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavaṃyeva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, no ca kho bhikkhū ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu; "
msgstr "“If Master Gotama was the only one to succeed in this teaching, not any monks, "

msgctxt "mn73:13.2"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena. "
msgstr "then this spiritual path would be incomplete in that respect. "

msgctxt "mn73:13.3"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako bhikkhū ca ārādhakā; "
msgstr "But because both Master Gotama and monks have succeeded in this teaching, "

msgctxt "mn73:13.4"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena. "
msgstr "this spiritual path is complete in that respect. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn73:13.5"
msgid "Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho bhikkhuniyo ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu; "
msgstr "If Master Gotama and the monks were the only ones to succeed in this teaching, not any nuns … "

msgctxt "mn73:13.6"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:13.7"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:13.8"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "mn73:13.9"
msgid "Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho upāsakā gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu; "
msgstr "celibate laymen … "

msgctxt "mn73:13.10"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:13.11"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:13.12"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "mn73:13.13"
msgid "Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho upāsakā gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu; "
msgstr "laymen enjoying sensual pleasures … "

msgctxt "mn73:13.14"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:13.15"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:13.16"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ paripūraṃ tenaṅgena. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.493, sc15
msgctxt "mn73:13.17"
msgid "Sace hi, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako abhavissa, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā abhavissaṃsu, no ca kho upāsikā gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā abhavissaṃsu; "
msgstr "celibate laywomen … "

msgctxt "mn73:13.18"
msgid "evamidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ aparipūraṃ abhavissa tenaṅgena. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn73:13.19"
msgid "Yasmā ca kho, bho gotama, imaṃ dhammaṃ bhavañceva gotamo ārādhako, bhikkhū ca ārādhakā, bhikkhuniyo ca ārādhikā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā brahmacārino ārādhakā, upāsakā ca gihī odātavasanā kāmabhogino ārādhakā, upāsikā ca gihiniyo odātavasanā brahmacāriniyo ārādhikā; "
