#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.494, sc17
msgctxt "mn73:13.25"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, gaṅgā nadī samuddaninnā samuddapoṇā samuddapabbhārā samuddaṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati, evamevāyaṃ bhoto gotamassa parisā sagahaṭṭhapabbajitā nibbānaninnā nibbānapoṇā nibbānapabbhārā nibbānaṃ āhacca tiṭṭhati. "
msgstr "Just as the Ganges river slants, slopes, and inclines towards the ocean, and keeps pushing into the ocean, in the same way Master Gotama’s assembly—with both laypeople and renunciates—slants, slopes, and inclines towards extinguishment, and keeps pushing into extinguishment. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15
msgctxt "mn73:15.1"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr "Excellent, Master Gotama! … "

msgctxt "mn73:15.2"
msgid "esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca. "
msgstr "I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "mn73:15.3"
msgid "Labheyyāhaṃ bhoto gotamassa santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti. "
msgstr "Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16
msgctxt "mn73:16.1"
msgid "“Yo kho, vaccha, aññatitthiyapubbo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhati pabbajjaṃ, ākaṅkhati upasampadaṃ, so cattāro māse parivasati. Catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya; "
msgstr "“Vaccha, if someone formerly ordained in another sect wishes to take the going forth, the ordination in this teaching and training, they must spend four months on probation. When four months have passed, if the mendicants are satisfied, they’ll give the going forth, the ordination into monkhood. "

msgctxt "mn73:16.2"
msgid "api ca mettha puggalavemattatā viditā”ti. "
msgstr "However, I have recognized individual differences in this matter.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:16.3"
msgid "“Sace, bhante, aññatitthiyapubbā imasmiṃ dhammavinaye ākaṅkhantā pabbajjaṃ, ākaṅkhantā upasampadaṃ cattāro māse parivasanti, catunnaṃ māsānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājenti upasampādenti bhikkhubhāvāya; ahaṃ cattāri vassāni parivasissāmi. Catunnaṃ vassānaṃ accayena āraddhacittā bhikkhū pabbājentu upasampādentu bhikkhubhāvāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, if four months probation are required in such a case, I’ll spend four years on probation. When four years have passed, if the mendicants are satisfied, let them give me the going forth, the ordination into monkhood.” "

msgctxt "mn73:16.4"
msgid "Alattha kho vacchagotto paribbājako bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ alattha upasampadaṃ. "
msgstr "And the wanderer Vaccha received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, sc18
msgctxt "mn73:17.1"
msgid "Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā vacchagotto addhamāsūpasampanno yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā vacchagotto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Not long after his ordination, a fortnight later, Venerable Vacchagotta went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn73:17.2"
msgid "“yāvatakaṃ, bhante, sekhena ñāṇena sekhāya vijjāya pattabbaṃ, anuppattaṃ taṃ mayā; "
msgstr "“Sir, I’ve reached as far as possible with the knowledge and understanding of a trainee. "

#. VAR: uttari ca me → uttariṃ me (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn73:17.3"
msgid "uttari ca me bhagavā dhammaṃ desetū”ti. "
msgstr "Please teach me further.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya18, sc19
msgctxt "mn73:18.1"
msgid "“Tena hi tvaṃ, vaccha, dve dhamme uttari bhāvehi—samathañca vipassanañca. "
msgstr "“Well then, Vaccha, further develop two things: serenity and discernment. "

msgctxt "mn73:18.2"
msgid "Ime kho te, vaccha, dve dhammā uttari bhāvitā—samatho ca vipassanā ca—anekadhātupaṭivedhāya saṃvattissanti. "
msgstr "When you have further developed these two things, they’ll lead to the penetration of many elements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, sc20
#. VAR: yāvadeva → yāvade (pts1)
msgctxt "mn73:19.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi: "
msgstr "Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case: "

msgctxt "mn73:19.2"
msgid "‘anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhaveyyaṃ—ekopi hutvā bahudhā assaṃ, bahudhāpi hutvā eko assaṃ; āvibhāvaṃ, tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gaccheyyaṃ, seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ kareyyaṃ, seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gaccheyyaṃ, seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kameyyaṃ, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parimaseyyaṃ, parimajjeyyaṃ; yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteyyan’ti, "
msgstr "‘May I wield the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying myself and becoming one again; appearing and disappearing; going unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and out of the earth as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; flying cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with my hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful; controlling my body as far as the Brahmā realm.’ "

msgctxt "mn73:19.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (1) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya20, pts-vp-pli1.495, sc21
msgctxt "mn73:20.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi: "
msgstr "Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case: "

msgctxt "mn73:20.2"
msgid "‘dibbāya sotadhātuyā visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇeyyaṃ—dibbe ca mānuse ca, ye dūre santike cā’ti, tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (2) "
msgstr "‘With clairaudience that is purified and superhuman, may I hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or far.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya21, sc22
msgctxt "mn73:21.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi: "
msgstr "Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case: "

msgctxt "mn73:21.2"
msgid "‘parasattānaṃ parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajāneyyaṃ—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ sarāgaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ vītarāgaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ sadosaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ vītadosaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; samohaṃ vā cittaṃ samohaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vītamohaṃ vā cittaṃ vītamohaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ saṅkhittaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ vikkhittaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ mahaggataṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ amahaggataṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ sauttaraṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ anuttaraṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; samāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ samāhitaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ asamāhitaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ; vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ cittanti pajāneyyaṃ, avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ avimuttaṃ cittanti pajāneyyan’ti, "
msgstr "‘May I understand the minds of other beings and individuals, having comprehended them with my mind. May I understand mind with greed as “mind with greed”, and mind without greed as “mind without greed”; mind with hate as “mind with hate”, and mind without hate as “mind without hate”; mind with delusion as “mind with delusion”, and mind without delusion as “mind without delusion”; constricted mind as “constricted mind”, and scattered mind as “scattered mind”; expansive mind as “expansive mind”, and unexpansive mind as “unexpansive mind”; mind that is not supreme as “mind that is not supreme”, and mind that is supreme as “mind that is supreme”; mind immersed in samādhi as “mind immersed in samādhi”, and mind not immersed in samādhi as “mind not immersed in samādhi”; freed mind as “freed mind”, and unfreed mind as “unfreed mind”.’ "

msgctxt "mn73:21.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (3) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya22, sc23
msgctxt "mn73:22.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi: "
msgstr "Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case: "

msgctxt "mn73:22.2"
msgid "‘anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyyaṃ, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi; anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe—amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapannoti; iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussareyyan’ti, "
msgstr "‘May I recollect many kinds of past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. May I remember: “There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.” May I recollect my many past lives, with features and details.’ "

msgctxt "mn73:22.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (4) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya23, pts-vp-pli1.496, sc24
msgctxt "mn73:23.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi: "
msgstr "Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case: "

msgctxt "mn73:23.2"
msgid "‘dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passeyyaṃ cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajāneyyaṃ—ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā; ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannāti; iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passeyyaṃ cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajāneyyan’ti, "
msgstr "‘With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, may I see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place—and understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds: “These dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they chose to act out of that wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. These dear beings, however, did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they chose to act out of that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.” And so, with clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, may I see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. And may I understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds.’ "

msgctxt "mn73:23.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane. (5) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya24, sc25
msgctxt "mn73:24.1"
msgid "So tvaṃ, vaccha, yāvadeva ākaṅkhissasi: "
msgstr "Whenever you want, you’ll be capable of realizing the following, in each and every case: "

msgctxt "mn73:24.2"
msgid "‘āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyan’ti, "
msgstr "‘May I realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with my own insight due to the ending of defilements.’ "

msgctxt "mn73:24.3"
msgid "tatra tatreva sakkhibhabbataṃ pāpuṇissasi, sati satiāyatane”ti. (6) "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya25, sc26
msgctxt "mn73:25.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vacchagotto bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinanditvā anumoditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "And then Venerable Vacchagotta approved and agreed with what the Buddha said. He got up from his seat, bowed, and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before leaving. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya26
msgctxt "mn73:26.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā vacchagotto eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi. "
msgstr "Then Vacchagotta, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:26.2"
msgid "“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi. "
msgstr "He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.” "

msgctxt "mn73:26.3"
msgid "Aññataro kho panāyasmā vacchagotto arahataṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "And Venerable Vacchagotta became one of the perfected. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya27, pts-vp-pli1.497, sc27
msgctxt "mn73:27.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ dassanāya gacchanti. "
msgstr "Now at that time several mendicants were going to see the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn73:27.2"
msgid "Addasā kho āyasmā vacchagotto te bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante. "
msgstr "Vacchagotta saw them coming off in the distance, "

msgctxt "mn73:27.3"
msgid "Disvāna yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca: "
msgstr "went up to them, and said, "

msgctxt "mn73:27.4"
msgid "“handa kahaṃ pana tumhe āyasmanto gacchathā”ti? "
msgstr "“Hello venerables, where are you going?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:27.5"
msgid "“Bhagavantaṃ kho mayaṃ, āvuso, dassanāya gacchāmā”ti. "
msgstr "“Reverend, we are going to see the Buddha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:27.6"
msgid "“Tenahāyasmanto mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vandatha, evañca vadetha: "
msgstr "“Well then, reverends, in my name please bow with your head to the Buddha’s feet and say: "

msgctxt "mn73:27.7"
msgid "‘vacchagotto, bhante, bhikkhu bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, evañca vadeti—"
msgstr "‘Sir, the mendicant Vacchagotta bows with his head to your feet and says, "

msgctxt "mn73:27.8"
msgid "pariciṇṇo me bhagavā, pariciṇṇo me sugato’”ti. "
msgstr "“I have served the Blessed One! I have served the Holy One!”’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya28
msgctxt "mn73:28.1"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato vacchagottassa paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn73:28.2"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then those mendicants went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn73:28.3"
msgid "“āyasmā, bhante, vacchagotto bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, evañca vadeti: "
msgstr "“Sir, the mendicant Vacchagotta bows with his head to your feet and says: "

msgctxt "mn73:28.4"
msgid "‘pariciṇṇo me bhagavā, pariciṇṇo me sugato’”ti. "
msgstr "‘I have served the Blessed One! I have served the Holy One!’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn73:28.5"
msgid "“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, vacchagotto bhikkhu cetasā ceto paricca vidito: "
msgstr "“I’ve already comprehended Vacchagotta’s mind and understood that "

msgctxt "mn73:28.6"
msgid "‘tevijjo vacchagotto bhikkhu mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo’ti. "
msgstr "he has the three knowledges, and is very mighty and powerful. "

msgctxt "mn73:28.7"
msgid "Devatāpi me etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ: "
msgstr "And deities also told me about this.” "

msgctxt "mn73:28.8"
msgid "‘tevijjo, bhante, vacchagotto bhikkhu mahiddhiko mahānubhāvo’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc28
msgctxt "mn73:28.9"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "mn73:28.10"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti. "
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn73:28.11"
msgid "Mahāvacchasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

